Psyche Library ("the App") is built and operated by Catalyst Behavioral Health Consulting LLC ("we", "us"). This Privacy Policy explains what data we collect, why, and how you can delete it.

────────────────────
1. WHAT WE COLLECT
────────────────────

Account data
• Email address
• Display name (optional)
• Password (stored only as a bcrypt hash — we cannot see your password)

Library data
• Articles you bookmark
• Searches you run and save
• Articles you open (history)
• AI literature reviews you generate
• Citation-graph "scrape" jobs you start

Device data (when you opt in to notifications)
• Expo push token associated with your account

We do NOT collect:
• Location, contacts, calendars, photos, microphone, or camera data
• Advertising identifiers (IDFA / GAID)
• Analytics or telemetry of how you use the app
• Health, biometric, or sensitive-category data

────────────────────
2. HOW WE USE IT
────────────────────

• To let you sign in across devices.
• To save your bookmarks, history, and saved searches.
• To send weekly research-digest emails IF you turn that on in Profile. You can turn it off any time.
• To send push notifications about saved-search matches IF you tap "Enable notifications" in Profile.
• To search third-party academic databases (PubMed, CrossRef, Europe PMC, OpenAlex, Semantic Scholar, DOAJ, arXiv) and the open web via Tavily, using only the query text you type — your account email is never sent to them.
• To generate AI summaries and literature reviews via Anthropic's Claude. Only article titles and abstracts are sent; your email and bookmarks are not.

────────────────────
3. WHO WE SHARE WITH
────────────────────

We share data only with the processors required to run the service:

• Resend (transactional email — for digest emails and password resets)
• Anthropic (Claude — for AI summaries; query + article excerpts only)
• Tavily (open-web search — query text only)
• MongoDB Atlas (database)
• Apple Push Notification service / Firebase Cloud Messaging (for push tokens — only if you enabled notifications)

We do NOT sell your data, share it for advertising, or use it to train AI models.

────────────────────
4. HOW LONG WE KEEP IT
────────────────────

We keep your account data until you delete your account. Anonymous summary caches (keyed only by article ID) may be retained to speed up the app for all users — these contain no personal data.

────────────────────
5. DELETING YOUR DATA
────────────────────

Open the app → Profile tab → "Delete account". This permanently removes:
• Your user record
• All bookmarks, history, saved searches, scrape jobs
• All password-reset records
• Your push token (if any)

Deletion is immediate and irreversible. There is no separate web form to fill out; everything happens inside the app, per Apple Guideline 5.1.1(v).

If you cannot reach the app for any reason, email support@catalystbhconsulting.com from the account's email address and we will delete the account within 5 business days.

────────────────────
6. CHILDREN
────────────────────

Psyche Library is intended for clinicians, researchers, and graduate students. It is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect data from them.

────────────────────
7. CONTACT
────────────────────

Questions or requests: support@catalystbhconsulting.com

